<h3 id="when-you-know-when-service-will-be-available">When you know when the service will be available</h2>

<p>Use this if you are planning to make the service unavailable for a short period and can tell people when it will be open again.</p>

{{ designExample({
  group: "patterns",
  item: "service-unavailable-page",
  type: "when-you-know-when-service-will-be-available"
}) }}

<p>If you are planning to make your service unavailable, if possible, give users advance warning of this on your service <a href="/design-system/patterns/start-page">start page</a>, above the "Start now" button.</p>

<div class="app-example app-example--content">
  {{ tag({
    text: "Example",
    classes: "app-example__heading"
  }) }}
  <h2 class="nhsuk-heading-s">Service unavailable tonight</h2>
  <p>This service will be temporarily unavailable from 11.59pm on 2 August to 2am on 3 August 2026.</p>
  <p>If you need urgent medical advice during this time, use <a href="#">111 online</a> or call 111.</p>

</div>
<p>During the time your service is unavailable, if you can, include a message on your start page to tell them when it will reopen.</p>
<div class="app-example app-example--content">
  {{ tag({
    text: "Example",
    classes: "app-example__heading"
  }) }}
  <h2 class="nhsuk-heading-s">Service unavailable now</h2>
  <p>This service is temporarily unavailable. You will be able to use it again from 2am on 3 August 2026.</p>
  <p>If you need urgent medical advice during this time, use <a href="#">111 online</a> or call 111.</p>

</div>

<p>If you are planning a longer closure, remove the Start button and make sure that any information users need during this time is on the service start page.</p>

<h3 id="updates">When you have updates about availability</h2>

<p>If the technical issue is unexpected, tell users:</p>
<ul>
  <li>any updates you have on progress to resolve it</li>
  <li>if possible, how long it might take</li>
</ul>
<p>Keep it updated if the situation changes.</p>

{{ designExample({
  group: "patterns",
  item: "service-unavailable-page",
  type: "with-update"
}) }}

<h3 id="standalone-page">Standalone page</h2>

<p>If you are using a proxy server or content delivery network (CDN), it will have a error page which is shown automatically whenever your service is unavailable.</p>

<p>As this page is hosted separately, you will need to configure a standalone error page which is not dependent on your service.</p>

<p>There is a <a href="#">standalone HTML template in the NHS frontend [fix link]</a>. You will need to edit it to add the name of your service and any relevant content to tell your users what to do if the service is unavailable.</p>

<h3 id="service-closed-permanently">Service closed permanently</h2>
<p>If your service is closing permanently, use a "This service is now closed" page. Refer users to another service or to somewhere that helps them deal with their problem.</p>
<p>Do not use a Page not found (404) page.</p>

{{ designExample({
  group: "patterns",
  item: "service-unavailable-page",
  type: "closed-replaced"
}) }}
<p>If users will look for your service, consider keeping the start page for a while but:</p>
<ul>
  <li>remove the start button</li>
  <li>explain to users how to get the help they need</li>
</ul>
<p>Take your start page down when users are no longer searching for it. Make sure that you also remove any links to the closed service.</p>

